CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 26, 1953, pg. 11, reads: "DEBS OF '53 - These charming post-debs are Santa's helper this year, as they busily prepare canned goods for needy families in district. From row, left to right: Barbara Pryor, social chairman; Willa Rogers, treasurer; Bernstine McClaney, president, and Rosaline Cobbs, secretary.  Back row, left to right, Jo Ann Snyder, Betty Scott, vice president; Gurlaine Smith and Harriet Wilds.  All were members of the 1953 Debutant Cotillion given last January by Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of eight women, first row left to right: Barbara Pryor, Willa Rogers, Bernstine McClaney, and Rosaline Cobbs wearing striped dress with light colored fur or angora collar; back row: Jo Ann Snyder, Betty Scott, Gurlaine Smith, and Harriet Wilds, gathered around brick patterned baskets of food, including Kent Farm canned goods, in domestic interior with matching lamps and venetian blind on window
